  <summary date="2019-01-25T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Federal Worker Credit Protection Act of 2019

This bill provides that, upon request by specified employees affected by the federal government shutdown that began on December 22, 2018, individuals are prohibited from reporting certain negative credit information to consumer reporting agencies.</summary>
